<% layout("layouts/boilerplate") %>
<style>
  .plastic-awareness-container {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-content {
    width: 80%;
    background: white;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.25rem auto;
    box-shadow: 0rem 0rem 0.625rem rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-radius: 0.625rem;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-img {
    height: auto;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 45rem;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-header {
    text-align: center;
    color: #2c3e50;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-section,
  .plastic-benefits-section {
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-section div {
    background: #ecf0f1;
    padding: 0.9375rem;
    margin: 0.9375rem 0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-title,
  .plastic-awareness-subtitle {
    color: #2980b9;
  }
  .plastic-awareness-list {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .plastic-benefits-list {
    background: #dff9fb;
    padding: 0.9375rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .plastic-awareness-content {
      width: 90%;
      padding: 1rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .plastic-awareness-content {
      width: 95%;
      padding: 0.75rem;
    }
    .plastic-awareness-header {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
    .plastic-awareness-title {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
    p,
    li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
  <div class="plastic-awareness-content">
    <h1 class="plastic-awareness-header">
      Plastic Pollution Awareness - Save Our Planet!
    </h1>
    <div class="plastic-awareness-section">
      <div>
        <h4 class="plastic-awareness-title">
          1. Why is plastic pollution a problem?
        </h4>
        <p>
          Plastic waste doesn’t decompose easily—it can take hundreds or even
          thousands of years to break down...
        </p>
        <img
          src="/images/img1.jpg"
          alt="Plastic Pollution"
          class="plastic-awareness-img"
        />
        <h6 class="plastic-awareness-subtitle">Key Facts</h6>
        <ul class="plastic-awareness-list">
          <li>8 million tons of plastic enter the ocean every year.</li>
          <li>
            1 million seabirds and 100,000 marine animals die from plastic
            pollution annually.
          </li>
          <li>Less than 10% of plastic is actually recycled.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="plastic-awareness-title">
          2. How can we reduce plastic waste in our daily lives?
        </h4>
        <p>
          By using reusable items, recycling properly, and reducing single-use
          plastics...
        </p>
        <img
          src="/images/img2.jpg"
          alt="Reduce Plastic Waste"
          class="plastic-awareness-img"
        />
        <h6 class="plastic-awareness-subtitle">Key Facts</h6>
        <ul class="plastic-awareness-list">
          <li>A single plastic bag takes up to 1,000 years to decompose.</li>
          <li>
            By switching to reusable bottles, an average person can save 167
            plastic bottles per year.
          </li>
          <li>
            More than 500 billion plastic bags are used worldwide every year.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="plastic-awareness-title">
          3. What happens to the plastic we throw away?
        </h4>
        <p>
          Most plastic ends up in landfills or the ocean, where it harms
          wildlife and pollutes the environment...
        </p>
        <img
          src="/images/img3.jpg"
          alt="Plastic Waste Impact"
          class="plastic-awareness-img"
        />
        <h6 class="plastic-awareness-subtitle">Key Facts</h6>
        <ul class="plastic-awareness-list">
          <li>More than 90% of plastic waste has never been recycled.</li>
          <li>
            There is currently more plastic in the ocean than fish by weight in
            some areas.
          </li>
          <li>It takes a plastic bottle 450 years to decompose in nature.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="plastic-benefits-section">
      <h1 class="plastic-awareness-header">Benefits of Recycling</h1>
      <ul class="plastic-benefits-list">
        <li>Reduces waste in landfills and prevents pollution</li>
        <li>Saves natural resources like trees, water, and minerals</li>
        <li>Decreases energy consumption and reduces greenhouse gases</li>
        <li>Helps protect wildlife and marine ecosystems</li>
        <li>Creates jobs and supports the economy</li>
        <li>Promotes a sustainable future for generations to come</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
